    • Constructor Detail

      • FF3_1

        public FF3_1(byte[] key,
             byte[] twk,
             int radix)
        Constructs a new context object for the FF3-1 algorithm.
        Parameters:
        key - a byte array containing the key
        twk - a byte array containing the "tweak" or iv. this value may not be null, and the number of bytes must be 7
        radix - the radix of the alphabet used for the plain and cipher text inputs/outputs

      • encrypt

        public java.lang.String encrypt(java.lang.String X,
                                byte[] twk)
        Encrypt a string, returning a cipher text using the same alphabet. The key, tweak parameters, and radix were all already set by the initialization of the FF3_1 object.
        Parameters:
        X - the plain text to be encrypted
        twk - the tweak used to perturb the encryption
        Returns:
        the encryption of the plain text, the cipher text

      • encrypt

      • decrypt

        public java.lang.String decrypt(java.lang.String X,
                                byte[] twk)
        Decrypt a string, returning the plain text. The key, tweak parameters, and radix were all already set by the initialization of the FF3_1 object.
        Parameters:
        X - the cipher text to be decrypted
        twk - the tweak used to perturb the encryption
        Returns:
        the decryption of the cipher text, the plain text
